ee</b>, a habitational name recorded in the 16th century as <i>Cudsee</i> and <i>Cutsee</i>, from a toponym located in Zeeland, which may be interpreted as <i>Cut's-see</i> ‘watercourse of Cudo’.","History: Dirk Coetzee, born in Kampen in the Netherlands around 1655, died in Cape Town in 1725."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gaucher de Thourotte was born in 1083, in Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, France, his father, Roger De Thourotte, was 34 and his mother, Alix de Montmorency, was 20. He married Mathilde DE ROULERS in 1102. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1142, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1083–1142":"1083–1142","1080–1148":"1080–1148","1108–1153":"1108–1153","1100–1172":"1100–1172","1119–1163":"1119–1163","1050–Male":"1050–Surnud","1063–1129":"1063–1129","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1142":"1142","1153":"1153","1163":"1163","1063":"1063","1172":"1172","1083":"1083","1050":"1050","1129":"1129","1148":"1148","1102":"1102","1100":"1100","1119":"1119","1108":"1108","Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Thourotte, Picardy, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1083–1142":"1083–1142","1080–1148":"1080–1148","1108–1153":"1108–1153","1100–1172":"1100–1172","1119–1163":"1119–1163","1050–Male":"1050–Kuollut","1063–1129":"1063–1129","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1142":"1142","1153":"1153","1163":"1163","1063":"1063","1172":"1172","1083":"1083","1050":"1050","1129":"1129","1148":"1148","1102":"1102","1100":"1100","1119":"1119","1108":"1108","Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, Ranska","Thourotte, Picardy, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1083–1142":"1083–1142","1080–1148":"1080–1148","1108–1153":"1108–1153","1100–1172":"1100–1172","1119–1163":"1119–1163","1050–Male":"1050–Décédé","1063–1129":"1063–1129","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1142":"1142","1153":"1153","1163":"1163","1063":"1063","1172":"1172","1083":"1083","1050":"1050","1129":"1129","1148":"1148","1102